entries.title: Tesla’s Profit Jumped 12% in Fourth Quarter
entries.description: The electric car company is facing intensifying competition, supply chain disruptions and concerns about the behavior of Elon Musk.

entries.title: Meta to Reinstate Trump’s Facebook and Instagram Accounts
entries.description: Donald Trump had been barred from the social media platforms after the Jan. 6, 2021, storming of the Capitol. Twitter reinstated him last year.

entries.title: Ukraine’s Scientists Receive a Funding Lifeline From Abroad
entries.description: The Simons Foundation in New York is providing annual grants to the country’s chemists, biologists, physicists and mathematicians.

entries.title: Microsoft Outlook and Teams Are Back Online After Morning Outages
entries.description: The widely used Microsoft Teams and Outlook email services were unavailable for thousands of users early Wednesday.

entries.title: Everyone Wants Your Email Address. Think Twice Before Sharing It.
entries.description: Your email address has become a digital bread crumb for companies to link your activity across sites. Here’s how you can limit this.

entries.title: Microsoft Revenue Up 2 Percent, but Profit Drops 12 Percent
entries.description: The company, which announced plans to lay off 10,000 workers last week, had warned that is was facing a significant slowdown in the growth of its sales.
